; Regression test for issue #2872
; https://github.com/ledger/ledger/issues/2872
;
; The original test for issue #1948 used "format 1000.000 CTG25" where
; CTG25 was intended as a mismatching commodity symbol. However, unquoted
; commodity names cannot contain digits (they terminate the symbol), so
; "CTG25" is silently parsed as "CTG". The 1948.test was updated to use
; "CTGBAR" to avoid this ambiguity.
;
; This file tests that an unquoted commodity name containing digits in a
; format directive produces a clear parse error naming the unexpected characters.

; Invalid: unquoted "CTG25" in a format directive — the parser reads "CTG"
; and stops at the digit, leaving "25" unconsumed.  This should be a clear
; diagnostic rather than silently truncating to "CTG" and then producing a
; confusing mismatch error against the wrong symbol.
commodity CTG
    format 1000.000 CTG25

2024/01/01 Test
    Expenses        1000.000 CTG
    Assets

test source -> 1
__ERROR__
While parsing file "$FILE", line 18:
Error: unexpected characters '25' after commodity symbol in format directive
end test
